## Verified Features

- ✅ Dark-mode 3-panel layout renders at 1400×860 with no overflow
- ✅ Image drop zone (drag/drop, paste, click) shows preview with remove button  
- ✅ Session timer starts on first interaction
- ✅ Mic button pulses red when "recording", waveform bars animate
- ✅ Live transcript types across the waveform bar character-by-character
- ✅ AI response streams into the bubble with a blinking cursor
- ✅ KaTeX math formulas render inline (LaTeX `$$…$$` delimiters)
- ✅ Hint (💡 cyan), Fallacy (⚠️ red), Theory (📖 yellow) callout cards appear after AI responses
- ✅ Flowchart adds a labelled node after each turn (green/red/yellow with icon ✓/✗/△)
- ✅ Missed step auto-inserts a yellow node mid-session
- ✅ Stats panel updates: Steps taken, Hints used, Errors caught, Accuracy %
- ✅ Reset button clears all state and restarts cleanly
- ✅ Zero browser console errors

---

## Next Steps for Hackathon Backend

1. **Gemini Live API** — replace mock mic loop with real `MediaRecorder` → WebSocket stream to Gemini Live
2. **Vision input** — send uploaded screenshot as image Part alongside voice stream
3. **Real-time AI parsing** — parse Gemini's streamed text for LaTeX delimiters and render mid-stream
4. **Progress tracking** — persist session to Firestore (Google Cloud) for cross-session continuity
5. **Google Cloud Run** — host the backend WebSocket relay
